text: Caribou County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 7,027 people lived there. The county seat and largest city is Soda Springs. == Communities == === Cities === * Bancroft * Grace * Soda Springs === Unincorporated communities === * Conda * Freedom * Henry * Wayan == References == Category:1919 establishments in Idaho Category:Idaho counties
